 run."{&1310}\par "But you were," I said.{&1310}\par "Not according to the story I spread with my brothers and sisters. It should have them assuming I faked a shift cover due to illness. They'd interview them first."{&1310}\par "Why?"{&1310}\par "Badge unaccounted for," he explained, picking a ruined bit of metal out of a drawer. The rest of the uniform he'd tossed as soon as we got away from the train. "They want me to come down as soon as I'm no longer contagious. They'll figure me out soon."{&1310}\par "So what are we gonna do then?" Tess chimed in again, still crouched behind the bathroom door and whispering across to us.{&1310}\par "Wait for them to leave," he said. "Get out of here. After that, I don't ... I don't really know. Get those coats on!"{&1310}\par \pard\sl0\slmult1\cf2\f1 {&1310}\par \pard\fi720\sl480\slmult1\cf1\f0 {&1310}\par \pard\sl0\slmult1\cf2\f1 {&1310}\par }{&1310}
