th, officer."{&1310}\par "Come out or I'll shoot him."{&1310}\par There was the telltale sing of a firebolt being prep'ed, and I imagined it pointed right at Richter's head.{&1310}\par "Then I'll come in there and shoot \i you\i0 ."{&1310}\par I stuck a hand out into the open doorway so he could see before anyone else could do anything. It happened so fast, I half-expected it to get melted right off to blinding fire as I did. And I waited against it, eyes squeezed shut.{&1310}\par "Okay. The rest of you."{&1310}\par Tess was next to me and trying to pull me back with her wide, desperate eyes. I pushed her away with a stern look that I couldn't even fake just then for the life of me. My head started spinning with flashes of that firebolt blasting away pieces of me as I crept them slowly out into view. My body started shaking on its own.{&1310}\par I tried to look up at the man, but all I could see was that gun pointed at my chest. It felt like gravity would suck that shot right out of the barrel and punch it through me if he didn't. And I waited for him too, holding both my hands up so he could see I didn't have any weapons to worry about.{&1310}\par {&1310}\par {&1310}\par When I came back around, Richter was standing in front of me.{&1310}\par And I must have fallen over backward in surprise because the next thing I knew Iw as on the floor.{&1310}\par "Are you alright?" he was demanding anxiously over me. I glanced past to the apartment door, but it was closed. Whatever'd been outside - they were gone now.{&1310}\par He helped me back up while Tess came out of hiding. I pushed past the man and went for my gun before he could say anything else.{&1310}\par "What'd they want?" Tess whispered, huddling by the bathroom door and throwing looks toward the front one like they might come barging through anyways. Maybe they would.{&1310}\par "Investigations," Richter said in flat tones, but I could tell they had him unnerved. "Wondering why I wasn't on the job for the Shtess